    (per-frame multiple contact points, micro-separation followed by re-
    contact, etc.). The result was Slomo / Squash / Knockback firing
    repeatedly and the +100 score being awarded multiple times for one
    hit.
    
    WalkingPerson.lua now gates OnHit at the entry point with a 0.5s
    time cooldown (HIT_COOLDOWN). The cooldown is the single source of
    truth for "is this a new hit?", so Slomo / score / future effects do
    not need to repeat the guard themselves. After the cooldown the same
    pedestrian can be hit again and the effects + score retrigger as
    expected.
    
    Tick now advances elapsedTime above the isMoving early-return so the
    cooldown still progresses while the pedestrian is stopped after a hit.
    The existing hasPlayedHitAction / OnEndHit pair is kept as the
    "separated then re-engaged" gate; cooldown and that flag answer
    different questions.

