    fix: editor billboards leaking into Game build
    
    UPrimitiveComponent::CreateRenderState skips proxy creation when
    IsEditorOnly() is true and the owning World's WorldType is not Editor.
    The check was running with the *default* WorldType (Editor) during
    scene load: LoadSceneFromJSON freshly constructs UWorld (which
    defaults to EWorldType::Editor), then deserializes actors. Adding
    each component fires CreateRenderState immediately, so editor-only
    billboards (light icons, decal/fog markers) got SceneProxies before
    GameEngine had a chance to flip the type to Game. The later
    SetWorldType(Game) doesn't retroactively destroy those proxies, so
    the icons stayed visible the whole match in Game builds. PIE wasn't
    affected because PIE actors come in via the Duplicate path on a
    World whose type is already PIE.
    
    Fix:
    - LoadSceneFromJSON now takes an optional `const EWorldType*
      OverrideWorldType`; if non-null it wins over the JSON's WorldType.
      The selected WorldType is applied via World->SetWorldType *before*
      InitWorld and actor deserialization, so CreateRenderState sees the
      final type and the editor-only guard works.
    - UGameEngine::LoadSceneFromPath passes EWorldType::Game as the
      override.
    
    Editor / PIE paths are unchanged.
    
