    fix: PIE re-entry crash, shutdown crash, and F8-eject hidden cursor
    
    Three small fixes around the PIE lifecycle that all surfaced after
    the recent UI/cursor refactors:
    
    1. PIE 2nd run crash inside CloseDocument
       UEditorEngine::EndPlayMap calls UUIManager::ClearViewport, which
       used to also DestroyObject every widget in CreatedWidgets. The
       Lua-side widgets[] table caches those pointers; on the 2nd PIE
       run UIManager.Init's re-entry branch hides them, dereferencing
       freed widgets and crashing inside Document->Close().
       Fix: split UUIManager::ClearViewport (viewport-only — keeps
       widget UObjects alive across PIE end / scene transition) from a
       new DestroyAllWidgets that also deletes the UObjects, and call
       the latter only from Shutdown.
    
    2. Shutdown crash inside ~UUserWidget
       UEngine::Shutdown ran FLuaScriptManager::Shutdown before
       UUIManager::Shutdown. UUserWidget owns FWidgetClickEventListener
       instances whose sol::protected_function destructors try to deref
       a lua_State; once the Lua VM is gone, those derefs hit freed
       memory.
       Fix: swap the order — UI tears down first while Lua is still
       live, then Lua VM goes.
    
    3. F8 eject leaves cursor hidden
       FEditorViewportClient::Tick only forwarded ProcessInput to the
       PIEViewportClient when IsPIEPossessedMode() was true. After the
       WantsMouse refactor moved cursor visibility entirely into
       UGameViewportClient::ProcessInput, eject mode no longer ran the
       "release cursor" branch — capture state from the previous
       possess frame just stuck.
       Fix: call ProcessInput in both possess and eject modes; keep the
       early return for possess so the editor camera doesn't fight game
       input. ProcessInput's existing !bInputPossessed branch then
       ShowCursor(TRUE) + ClipCursor(nullptr) automatically.
    
